  <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Financial support from the government.</h3>


  <div class="govuk-notification-banner govuk-notification-banner--git" role="region" aria-labelledby="govuk-notification-banner-title" data-module="govuk-notification-banner" style="border-left-color: #f9b400;">
    <div class="govuk-notification-banner__content govuk-notification-banner__content--grey">
       <h4 class="govuk-heading-m">Bursary</h4>
        <p class="govuk-body">This course has a bursary of £25,000 available to eligible trainees.</p>

         <p class="govuk-body"> To be eligible for a bursary, you’ll need at least one of the following:
          <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
            <li>a bachelor’s degree class 2:2 (honours) or higher</li>
            <li>a master’s degree</li>
            <li>a PhD</li>
          </ul>
        </p>

        <p class="govuk-body">If you are eligible you will receive the bursary automatically, you do not need to apply for it.</p>

        <p class="govuk-body"><a href="https://getintoteaching.education.gov.uk/funding-and-support/scholarships-and-bursaries">Find out whether you are eligible for a bursary</a></p>

        <p class="govuk-body">If you're a non-UK citizen without indefinite leave to remain, you will usually not be eligible for a bursary. <a href="https://getintoteaching.education.gov.uk/non-uk-teachers/fees-and-funding-for-non-uk-trainees">Find out about fees and funding for non-UK citizens.</a></p>
